supportDesc.extent: 52 leaves : 170 x 120 (150 x 95) mm, bound to 180 x 125 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Between 11 and 16 lines per page; sometimes in two columns, sometimes with couplets staggered.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in an squarish naskh in black ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

decoNote: Section titles boxed in black lines.

origin.p: Item is not dated, but probably copied in the late 18th or 19th century by ʻAlī ʻĀs̜iḳ Ṣāfī (f. 52r).

provenance: Formerly owned by George A. Plimpton (bookplate inside front cover).
